<HEADLINE> Burn 2, Wizards 1, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Mark Dodd held the Kansas City Wizards  
scoreless in a shootout to lead the Dallas Burn to a 2-1 win 
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Ted Eck scored for the Burn (16-13) in the 75th minute of the  
second half from 18 yards out for a 1-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Alexi Lalas countered 11 minutes later for the Wizards (8-21),  
sending in a diving header with four minutes remaining in the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Richard Farer, Jorge Rodriguez and John Jairo Trellez scored for  
Dallas in the shootout. 
</P>
<P>
	Dallas leads the series between the teams 9-7.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
