<HEADLINE> Mr. Greeley Sold for $725,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Aaron U. Jones and his wife paid a session  
high $725,000 Saturday for a filly by Mr. Greeley at Keeneland's 
September Yearling Sale. 
</P>
<P>
	Dixiana Farm Inc., as agent for Stoneworth Farm, sold the dark  
bay or brown filly out of Final Deputy, by Deputy Minister. She is 
a half sister to stakes-placed Private Deputy. 
</P>
<P>
	A stakes winner of five races and $474,452, Mr. Greeley's first  
foals are 2-year-olds this year. 
</P>
<P>
	A daughter of Cherokee Run brought $325,000, the second high  
price of the session Saturday. J.S. Moss and his wife purchased the 
bay filly. 
</P>
<P>
	Cherokee Run is the sire of undefeated Chilukki, one of the top  
2-year-old fillies in North America. 
</P>
<P>
	During Saturday's session, Keeneland sold 289 horses for  
$14,264,700, an average of $49,359. The median was $35,000. 
</P>
<P>
	At last year's corresponding session, 305 horses brought  
$10,384,300, an average of $34,047. The median was $26,000. 
</P>
<P>
	After six days of the 11-day auction, 1,634 horses have been  
sold for a sales record $202,777,200, an average of $124,099 and a 
median of $62,000. 
</P>
<P>
	At this point in last year's sale, 1,693 horses had been sold  
for $150,014,500. The average was $88,609 and the median was 
$50,000. 
</P>
<P>
	The sale continues through Thursday.  
  	   	
</P>
