<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Diamondbacks 8, Marlins 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Luis Gonzalez hit a two-run homer in the 10th  
inning, and the Arizona Diamondbacks beat the Florida Marlins 8-6 
Saturday, reducing their magic number for clinching the NL West to 
eight. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, in a 2-for-33 slide before the home run, became the  
third Diamondback with 100 RBIs this season. Jay Bell has 103 and 
Matt Williams has 132. 
</P>
<P>
	Randy Johnson struck out seven in six innings, raising his major  
league-leading total to 342, the sixth-highest total in a season, 
one more than Nolan Ryan fanned in 1977. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona, which has won 10 of 13, increased its lead to seven  
games over second-place San Francisco, which lost to San Diego 
11-5. 
</P>
<P>
	Bell led off the 10th with an infield single off Hector Almonte  
(0-1). Gonzalez then hit a 1-2 pitch into the pool in right-center 
field for his 25th homer of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Greg Swindell (4-0) pitched the 10th for the win.  
</P>
<P>
	Mike Lowell homered twice for Florida, which has lost eight of  
nine. His three-run shot off Matt Mantei with two outs in the ninth 
put the Marlins ahead 6-5. Mantei had not allowed a home run since 
Arizona acquired him from Florida on July 9. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona tied it in the bottom half on Henley Frias' leadoff  
triple off Antonio Alfonseca and Damian Miller's sacrifice fly. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson blanked the Marlins until Lowell hit a two-run homer in  
the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
	Steve Finley hit his career-best 31st home run and Miller also  
homered for the Diamondbacks. 
</P>
<P>
	The Diamondbacks took a 4-0 lead in the fourth against Brian  
Meadows on rookie Erubiel Durazo's first career triple and Finley's 
two-run homer. 
</P>
<P>
 *Notes:* Johnson has pitched a career-high 255 2-3 innings. He  
pitched 255 1-3 in 1993 for Seattle. ... Next up for Johnson on the 
single-season strikeout list is Bob Feller, who struck out 348 in 
1946. Ryan set the record of 383 in 1973. ... Lee had four hits. 
... Tony Womack stole his major league-leading 68th base in the 
fifth inning. ... Umpire Kerwin Danley, who took a foul ball off 
his foot in Colorado earlier in the week, skipped his turn behind 
the plate and instead worked first base for the second straight 
game. ... Arizona purchased the contract of C Rod Barajas from 
Double-A El Paso of the Texas League and placed LHP Brian Shouse on 
the 60-day disabled list. Barajas hit .318 with 14 homers and 95 
RBIs for the Diablos this season. 
  	   	
</P>
