<HEADLINE> Rapids 1, Galaxy 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Jorge Dely Valdes scored the game's only goal to  
lead the Colorado Rapids to a 1-0 victory over Los Angeles on 
Saturday night, snapping the Galaxy's three-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
	Dely Valdes' goal, in the 41st minute, broke a four-game home  
drought for the Rapids who had not scored at Mile High Stadium 
since July 28. 
</P>
<P>
	Matt McKeon sent a pass to a charging Paul Bravo who took a shot  
that ricocheted off defender Paul Caligiuri. Dely Valdes got the 
rebound and put it past Kevin Hartman who managed to get a hand on 
the game-winning shot, but couldn't keep it out of the net. 
</P>
<P>
	The Galaxy (18-10), who had several scoring opportunities,  
remained in first place in the Western Conference as the Rapids 
(18-9) moved back into second place, only two points behind. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
