<HEADLINE> Crew 1, Revolution 0, Shootout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- Ansil Elcock scored the deciding goal of a  
shootout Saturday night as the Columbus Crew defeated the New 
England Revolution 1-0. 
</P>
<P>
	Jeff Cunningham, Stern John and Robert Warzycha also converted  
in the 4-1 shootout for the Crew, while Joe-Max Moore found the net 
for New England. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither team scored in regulation. Columbus is 17-11 while New  
England (10-19) has won just twice since the All-Star break. The 
Revolution are trying for the fourth and final playoff spot in the 
Eastern Conference and are fifth, one point behind Miami, which 
plays San Jose on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Before the shoot, New England coach Walter Zenga had to be  
restrained by Revolution officials after getting into an argument 
with referee Ted Covaciu. 
  	   	
</P>
