</P>
<P>
	Despite the presence of Griffey and Rodriguez, two of baseball's  
top players, the Mariners took a 72-74 record into their final 
homestand on Friday night and were in third place in the AL West 
for the second straight year. They started the season with a $53 
million players' payroll. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's never enough money,'' Ellis said. ``I'm sure Woody and  
anybody else would agree that there's never enough money.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Woodward's departure brings speculation about the future of  
Piniella, who will no longer have a strong supporter in the front 
office. 
</P>
<P>
	``Let's not talk about my situation,'' Piniella said. ``This is  
Woody's day.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
