<HEADLINE> United 2, MetroStars 1, OT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Jeff Agoos scored the winning goal as D.C.  
United beat the New York/NewJersey MetroStars 2-1 in a shootout 
Saturday night and extended their unbeaten streak to a team-record 
10 straight. 
</P>
<P>
	Moreno's 42nd-minute goal, his fifth in the eight games, put  
United ahead 1-0. Richie Williams and Ben Olsen assisted on 
Moreno's 10th goal of the season. He has been involved in 10 of the 
past 11 goals for United in a five-game span. 
</P>
<P>
	Peter Villegas tied it in the 48th minute, getting his third  
goal of the season off assists by Ramiro Corrales and Eduardo 
Hurtado. 
</P>
<P>
	Jaime Moreno and Agoos connected in the shootout for United  
(22-7), which has the best record in the league and is 17-1 against 
conference opponents. 
</P>
<P>
	Brian Kelly scored in the shootout for the MetroStars (6-23),  
who have lost 12 of 13 and 18 of 20. In their previous game, the 
MetroStars beat Columbus 2-1 to stop a 12-game losing streak. 
</P>
<P>
	D.C.'s Roy Lassiter, who has 17 goals this season, had a goal  
disallowed when he was called offsides with just over 10 minutes 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	United already has clinched the Eastern Conference title and  
homefield advantage throughout the playoffs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
