<HEADLINE> Injured Piazza Misses Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Mike Piazza did not start the New York Mets'  
game Saturday night against the Philadelphia Phillies because of a 
bruised left hand. 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza left Friday night's game before the second inning after  
being hit in his catching hand by a foul ball from Ron Gant. 
</P>
<P>
	``It feels better than last night,'' Piazza said before  
Saturday's game. ``The swelling has gone down, but there is a 
little numbness in the thumb. Doctors said that's normal for the 
injury.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza, the Mets most dangerous hitter, is hitting .314 with 35  
homers and 114 RBIs. The Mets can ill afford to be without for him 
for long as they pursue Atlanta in the NL East and try to hold off 
Cincinnati for the wild card. 
</P>
<P>
	``No question, it's frustrating,'' Piazza said. ``I've been  
through this before. I want to make sure I go in when I know I can 
play rather than not being able to feel the bat in my hand and try 
to go.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Piazza is expected to play Sunday, but with a day off Monday,  
the Mets could wait to bring back the All-Star catcher until they 
begin a three-game series Tuesday at Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't want to come back until I know I can contribute,'' he  
said. 
  	   	
</P>
